Do you want some young radish?

553
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:40,972
She smiles well, too.

554
00:35:41,055 --> 00:35:42,223
Do you have no makeup on?

555
00:35:43,349 --> 00:35:46,936
Oh, I got a little busy,
so I stopped in the middle.

556
00:35:47,019 --> 00:35:48,729
You think you're pretty, don't you?

557
00:35:49,856 --> 00:35:51,065
-Pardon?
-Well,

558
00:35:51,732 --> 00:35:53,192
I just thought you would think so.

559
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:59,866
Well, I don't think I'm pretty.

560
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:03,953
But I do think that I'm not too awful
when it comes to my physiognomy.

561
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:05,872
Goodness, this is embarrassing.

562
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:08,499
I'm not here to talk about
your physiognomy.

563
00:36:09,125 --> 00:36:11,752
Legally speaking,
I just have to tell you a month before,

564
00:36:11,919 --> 00:36:14,463
but I thought I should tell you
a little more in advance.

565
00:36:15,339 --> 00:36:18,426
-What is it?
-Our contract expires in December.

566
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:20,928
-Yes.
-I need you to move out.

567
00:36:23,764 --> 00:36:25,433
Pardon? Move out? So suddenly?

568
00:36:25,516 --> 00:36:26,893
"Suddenly"? This isn't sudden.

569
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:29,854
The Lease Protection Act doesn't apply.
You have three months.

570
00:36:39,697 --> 00:36:44,035
Ms. Hong, if this is because
you wish to raise the rent,

571
00:36:44,118 --> 00:36:45,828
we can talk about it--

572
00:36:45,912 --> 00:36:47,997
No, I'm not going to raise the rent.

573
00:36:48,789 --> 00:36:51,209
It's a shop without any windows,
so once you move out,

574
00:36:51,292 --> 00:36:53,461
it'll just be used to
store dried seafood again.

575
