Then I'll probably only get
a quarter of what I get from you.

576
00:36:58,049 --> 00:37:00,092
Then why are you asking me to...

577
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:03,971
Money isn't the problem here.
Do I have to spell it out?

578
00:37:07,516 --> 00:37:11,312
You probably get what I mean,
so let's not talk about this anymore.

579
00:37:12,647 --> 00:37:15,274
Then go ahead and do what you were doing.

580
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:27,161
Gyu-tae is going to
want to go to Yangpyeong.

581
00:37:35,253 --> 00:37:36,545
Ms. Hong.

582
00:37:40,841 --> 00:37:45,554
Ms. Hong, Mr. No didn't say anything,

583
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:46,973
so I wasn't prepared.

584
00:37:47,056 --> 00:37:50,768
And he didn't say anything
the last time I met him.

585
00:37:50,893 --> 00:37:52,770
-He didn't--
-How dare you?

586
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:56,482
Are you using my husband
as your shield in front of me?

587
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:01,362
It's not like that.

588
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:03,155
Dongbaek.

589
00:38:03,864 --> 00:38:05,658
I want to be sophisticated to the end.

590
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:10,037
But if you keep provoking me
and I end up losing it,

591
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:12,707
I'd want to be straightforward with you.

592
00:38:13,749 --> 00:38:16,585
Then it'll make
both of us look very awful.

593
00:38:18,212 --> 00:38:20,339
So you need to be careful.

594
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:27,722
I don't like your skin,
the way you talk, and your physiognomy,

595
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:30,099
but that face is the worst.

596
00:38:30,850 --> 00:38:33,185
I hate that face which says,
"I don't know a thing."

597
00:38:37,064 --> 00:38:40,151
Do you get what I'm trying to tell you?

598
00:38:58,753 --> 00:38:59,795
Dongbaek!

599
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:03,883
What's wrong? What is it?

600
00:39:04,050 --> 00:39:05,760
Why do you look like a sad cow again?

601
00:39:05,843 --> 00:39:09,013
I stole a bag of red pepper powder
because I heard you're making kimchi.

602
00:39:09,096 --> 00:39:11,349
Why do you look so sad again?

603
00:39:12,558 --> 00:39:14,810
I think I got on my landlord's bad side.

604
00:39:16,479 --> 00:39:17,480
What?

605
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:25,613
LET'S READ TOGETHER,
SHARING AND REUSING CAMPAIGN

606
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:40,002
Darn it, why are there so many people?

607
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:45,174
Why isn't she coming to pick him up?

608
00:39:52,014 --> 00:39:54,600
Why did she let someone like her
look after her son?

609
00:39:56,143 --> 00:39:57,061
Darn it.

610
00:40:05,528 --> 00:40:06,612
Do you read?

611
00:40:07,238 --> 00:40:09,073
I was just told to take it.

612
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:12,076
-Where's Mom?
-We made kimchi today.

613
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:14,829
Then is Mom there alone?

614
00:40:15,663 --> 00:40:17,206
Did that policeman come today?

615
00:40:17,748 --> 00:40:19,208
Why? You don't like him?

616
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:21,794
I don't. Do you like him?

617
00:40:22,795 --> 00:40:25,297
I don't know. I'm not really sure
which side I'll take.

618
00:40:26,215 --> 00:40:29,093
But that policeman is
the fourth guy I hate.

619
00:40:29,176 --> 00:40:31,554
-The fourth?
-He comes after

620
00:40:31,637 --> 00:40:34,849
Mr. No Gyu-tae, Jun-gi's dad,
and the guy from the rice cake shop.

621
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:37,143
Then that means you like him best.

622
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:39,270
Why is my mom 48 kg?

623
00:40:39,895 --> 00:40:41,897
-What?
-Why is my mom so pretty?

624
00:40:42,606 --> 00:40:45,025
She's the prettiest mom in Ongsan.

625
00:40:45,734 --> 00:40:47,486
It really exhausts me.

626
00:40:48,654 --> 00:40:51,323
You're starting to make me want a son.

627
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:54,493
Let's go.

628
00:41:02,751 --> 00:41:04,712
Doesn't she have a car?

629
00:41:05,171 --> 00:41:07,006
I might as well just get her one.

630
00:41:07,673 --> 00:41:09,800
Pil-gu, should we ride a car
since it's hot?

631
00:41:10,342 --> 00:41:12,261
What car? Do you have a car?

632
00:41:12,344 --> 00:41:13,596
We'll just hitchhike.

633
00:41:18,559 --> 00:41:19,810
Kang Jong-ryeol!

634
00:41:21,896 --> 00:41:23,689
Is she seriously nuts?

635
00:41:31,655 --> 00:41:33,616
Yong-sik, what did your mother say?

636
00:41:34,074 --> 00:41:35,910
Is it okay to give this back to her?

637
00:41:38,787 --> 00:41:39,914
Is that my mom's?

638
00:41:41,415 --> 00:41:42,625
Just leave it here.

639
00:41:42,708 --> 00:41:45,753
I'll take it when I leave
and give it back to her.

640
00:41:48,005 --> 00:41:49,507
I guess I shouldn't go.

641
00:41:51,133 --> 00:41:54,386
My mom likes you.
You guys are best friends.

642
00:42:02,061 --> 00:42:04,396
Pil-gu and your mother
are both against this.

643
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:07,525
So stop being so stubborn,

644
00:42:08,317 --> 00:42:09,527
and stop liking me.

645
00:42:12,738 --> 00:42:14,823
I do kind of feel like

646
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:19,245
I should be more careful about how I act

647
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:22,665
for about two to three months.

648
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:27,253
I'm not an adolescent kid, you see.
If I totally ignore what my mom says,

649
00:42:27,336 --> 00:42:31,924
I don't think it'll do you any good
in the future.

650
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:34,718
So I'll make a strategic retreat...

651
00:42:35,010 --> 00:42:38,973
You really don't need
to explain everything to me.

652
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:41,183
What?

653
00:42:41,809 --> 00:42:45,563
There's one thing I learned
ever since I was really young.

654
00:42:47,314 --> 00:42:50,192
No one likes Dongbaek.
Who in the world would like me?

655
00:42:52,069 --> 00:42:53,946
I like you.

656
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:57,783
No, it's not like we actually dated.

657
00:42:59,326 --> 00:43:02,246
And even I wouldn't be happy
if Pil-gu fell for a woman like me.

658
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:08,002
But I'm really used to this,
so I'm totally fine with it.

659
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:11,672
I'll just let it go like I always did.

660
00:43:13,090 --> 00:43:17,011
You always remind me of a Whac-A-Mole.

661
00:43:18,178 --> 00:43:19,930
You're always smiling,

662
00:43:20,723 --> 00:43:23,767
but you're always hurting as well.

663
00:43:24,685 --> 00:43:27,396
You have no idea
how much it frustrates me.

664
00:43:30,608 --> 00:43:32,192
You should listen to your mother.

665
00:43:34,194 --> 00:43:37,406
No one else in this world
cares about you more than she does.

666
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:41,577
So stop acting like an adolescent
and act like an adult.

667
00:43:43,704 --> 00:43:44,747
Don't come here again.

668
00:43:53,505 --> 00:43:56,508
Does the air conditioner work properly?
Is it nice and cool?

669
00:43:58,636 --> 00:44:00,304
Shouldn't you be training?

670
00:44:00,387 --> 00:44:02,139
-What?
-Why do you come every day?

671
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:06,101
Maybe he has
something more important to do.

672
00:44:06,185 --> 00:44:08,729
Hey, why are you going through my car?

673
00:44:09,188 --> 00:44:11,231
By the way, the landlord
told us to move out.

674
00:44:12,066 --> 00:44:13,776
-Really?
-Don't worry.

675
00:44:13,859 --> 00:44:15,277
Your mom has a lot of connections.

676
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:18,405
If you have enough money,
just buy the building for her.

677
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:20,574
-You earn a lot of money.
-What?

678
00:44:21,992 --> 00:44:23,952
Why would I buy her that building?

679
00:44:25,037 --> 00:44:27,247
Should we talk about why?

680
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,504
I'm so glad I'm friends with Dongbaek.

681
00:44:34,421 --> 00:44:36,507
Why did you have to sit
in the passenger seat?

682
00:44:36,715 --> 00:44:39,176
Mr. Kang, I follow Jessica on Instagram.

683
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:42,638
-So?
-Ask her to follow me, too.

684
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:44,973
We might meet each other often
from now on.

