OK AESTHETIC

748
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:10,525
I think this is done.

749
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:14,196
That hoarse cough...

750
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:48,396
-Hey.
-Yes, sir?

751
00:51:49,606 --> 00:51:51,441
No need to go through the customer list.

752
00:51:52,526 --> 00:51:53,610
It obviously looks like

753
00:51:54,986 --> 00:51:56,696
it was his first time here.

754
00:52:08,333 --> 00:52:09,459
Would you have known

755
00:52:10,919 --> 00:52:12,712
that there'd be someone in here?

756
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:17,884
Even I don't know what this is.
He probably didn't know, either.

757
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:23,140
Why would he have made a mess
of the entire place

758
00:52:23,390 --> 00:52:25,350
after having murdered
the victim over there?

759
00:52:28,186 --> 00:52:30,188
It's because he failed to find Dongbaek.

760
00:52:33,567 --> 00:52:35,694
She should've just stayed still.

761
00:52:41,741 --> 00:52:44,744
Geum-ok, the door...

762
00:52:46,913 --> 00:52:47,873
Geum-ok.

763
00:52:50,750 --> 00:52:52,210
What's wrong with this?

764
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:55,046
Geum-ok, I'm all done.

765
00:52:55,589 --> 00:52:56,673
Geum-ok.

766
00:52:57,632 --> 00:52:59,009
I think it's over now.

767
00:53:01,219 --> 00:53:02,387
Geum-ok.

768
00:53:03,513 --> 00:53:07,684
OK AESTHETIC

769
00:53:12,105 --> 00:53:13,231
Geum-ok.

770
00:53:13,982 --> 00:53:15,025
Geum-ok.

771
00:53:16,860 --> 00:53:18,904
I think you should fix this. It's weird.

772
00:53:24,242 --> 00:53:26,244
Geum-ok, the door's really weird.

773
00:53:33,585 --> 00:53:34,628
The sound of his cough.

774
00:53:35,670 --> 00:53:38,882
His cough was persistent,
and it seemed uncontrollable.

775
00:53:38,965 --> 00:53:42,552
I still can't forget that peculiar cough.

776
00:53:55,440 --> 00:53:56,608
My gosh!

777
00:54:35,772 --> 00:54:37,899
PLEASE STOP BEING A JOKE...

778
00:54:37,983 --> 00:54:40,360
It's obvious that Joker was startled.

779
00:54:41,027 --> 00:54:44,823
This woman must've caught him off guard.

780
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:51,955
She always seemed so misfortunate.

781
00:54:52,038 --> 00:54:53,999
-Do you remember anything?
-How do you feel?

782
00:54:54,082 --> 00:54:56,584
-How did she survive?
-Hey, keep everyone in order!

783
00:55:00,714 --> 00:55:02,340
Isn't she the owner of the bar?

784
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:05,885
-Dongbaek?
-Yes, that's her.

785
00:55:06,303 --> 00:55:08,221
-You're right.
-What in the world happened?

786
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:18,523
Detective, I can't take this.

787
00:55:18,606 --> 00:55:22,360
I really can't live like this.

788
00:55:23,028 --> 00:55:25,947
A news reporter dropped by earlier,

789
00:55:26,031 --> 00:55:29,284
and a fortune teller even offered
to perform an exorcism for me

790
00:55:29,367 --> 00:55:30,618
to get rid of my bad luck.

791
00:55:31,619 --> 00:55:33,455
But you see,

792
00:55:34,456 --> 00:55:35,749
I really...

793
00:55:37,250 --> 00:55:39,669
didn't see anything.

794
00:55:41,004 --> 00:55:42,339
So there's nothing to tell.

795
00:55:43,006 --> 00:55:45,800
I just saw him from behind.

796
00:55:49,512 --> 00:55:51,222
Just leave me out of this.

797
00:55:51,890 --> 00:55:53,433
You can catch him without my help.

798
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:58,063
Dongbaek, then let me ask you
one more thing.

799
00:56:00,482 --> 00:56:02,359
Did the fire sprinkler really turn on

800
00:56:02,609 --> 00:56:05,236
right when he stood in front of you?

801
00:56:05,570 --> 00:56:07,697
He didn't turn it on
to get rid of any evidence?

802
00:56:08,156 --> 00:56:10,658
He really ran away
because it turned on all of a sudden?

803
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:12,869
Is that what happened?

804
00:56:14,371 --> 00:56:18,875
When the guy was standing in front of me,

805
00:56:19,292 --> 00:56:24,130
I heard the fire alarm go off
along with the fire sprinkler.

806
00:56:24,714 --> 00:56:27,675
-And I think someone knocked on the door.
-The door?

807
00:56:28,259 --> 00:56:33,014
Yes, but I'm really not sure.
Everything happened all of a sudden.

808
00:56:34,641 --> 00:56:38,937
But he was definitely
standing right in front of me.

809
00:56:42,565 --> 00:56:43,691
The fire sprinkler

810
00:56:43,775 --> 00:56:45,318
saved your life.

811
00:56:46,486 --> 00:56:47,529
What?

812
00:56:48,655 --> 00:56:50,490
But why did it go off
at that exact moment?

813
00:56:51,991 --> 00:56:54,869
Is that kind of coincidence even possible?

814
00:56:55,954 --> 00:56:56,996
REPORT OF INCIDENT

815
00:56:57,122 --> 00:56:59,040
OK AESTHETIC MURDER CASE
WITNESS STATEMENT

816
00:56:59,124 --> 00:57:02,001
Dongbaek managed to live
thanks to whatever luck she had back then.

817
00:57:02,752 --> 00:57:04,003
But I'm worried about her.

818
00:57:04,879 --> 00:57:09,676
The entire neighborhood knew the witness.
So there's no way Joker didn't find out.

819
00:57:10,552 --> 00:57:13,805
So the great Joker
stopped murdering people

820
00:57:13,888 --> 00:57:15,473
after he met Dongbaek?

821
00:57:17,684 --> 00:57:21,354
Who knows if he stopped
or if he's just taking a break?

822
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:34,200
Anxiety needs to be exterminated.

823
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:38,163
We should find the root,
beat it into a pulp,

824
00:57:38,955 --> 00:57:40,665
and burn it to ashes.

825
00:57:40,748 --> 00:57:42,208
What's wrong with your eyes?

826
00:57:42,292 --> 00:57:46,254
I'm not going to leave something uncertain
like luck to protect Dongbaek.

827
00:57:46,337 --> 00:57:47,380
Stop glaring like that.

828
00:57:47,464 --> 00:57:49,549
Chief.

829
00:57:50,717 --> 00:57:52,177
I'm going to catch Joker.

830
00:57:53,261 --> 00:57:56,514
I'll catch him and let him know
that he messed with the wrong person.

831
00:58:04,439 --> 00:58:06,649
-Hey!
-My gosh, you startled me.

832
00:58:07,192 --> 00:58:09,277
Why did you jaywalk? You're a cop.

833
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:11,738
Mom, what brings you here?

834
00:58:11,821 --> 00:58:14,407
I'm here to file a report.

835
00:58:14,491 --> 00:58:16,743
-A report for what?
-A thief broke into our house.

836
00:58:16,826 --> 00:58:17,827
What?

837
00:58:17,911 --> 00:58:20,747
Someone stole an entire bag
of red pepper powder.

838
00:58:21,414 --> 00:58:24,834
I'm going to take a look
at the security footage

839
00:58:24,918 --> 00:58:27,170
-and catch that son of a--
-Mom.

840
00:58:28,463 --> 00:58:30,089
-I took it.
-What?

841
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:31,841
I took it and gave it to Dongbaek.

842
00:58:33,968 --> 00:58:35,386
-Mom.
-Hey.

843
00:58:35,887 --> 00:58:37,847
I should file a report.
I won't forgive you.

844
00:58:37,931 --> 00:58:39,140
Mom, listen to me.

845
00:58:40,600 --> 00:58:41,684
You see...

846
00:58:42,810 --> 00:58:45,522
Gosh, I'm too embarrassed
to say this to you.

847
00:58:45,605 --> 00:58:46,773
Then don't say it.

848
00:58:46,856 --> 00:58:51,277
I can't do what you asked
and stay away from her for two months.

849
00:58:51,361 --> 00:58:52,570
I can't do that!

850
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:55,740
Gosh, Mom.

851
00:58:55,823 --> 00:58:57,992
Mom, stop... My gosh.

852
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:05,708
Mom, you can beat me all you want,
but I won't change my mind.

853
00:59:06,042 --> 00:59:08,044
You can think of me as an immature kid

854
00:59:08,127 --> 00:59:10,296
and hire some guys to beat me into a pulp,

855
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:13,007
but that's still not going to stop me
from liking Dongbaek.

856
00:59:15,051 --> 00:59:17,720
Are you saying you're going to choose her

857
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:20,557
over your own mother
who raised you for 30 years?

858
00:59:23,017 --> 00:59:27,313
Mom, I know what you mean.
I know you raised me for 30 years.

859
00:59:28,147 --> 00:59:30,108
But if I don't protect Dongbaek,

860
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:33,152
I'll regret it for the next 30 years.

861
00:59:33,987 --> 00:59:37,240
Why are you glaring like that again?

862
00:59:37,323 --> 00:59:39,993
Mom, I really mean it.

863
00:59:40,368 --> 00:59:43,162
I'm really sorry to say this.

864
00:59:44,372 --> 00:59:47,125
But you always let me do what I wanted
for the past 30 years.

865
00:59:47,250 --> 00:59:50,545
So let me do what I want again
just this once!

866
00:59:52,755 --> 00:59:56,467
What am I going to do with that darn punk?

867
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:58,553
CAMELLIA

868
01:00:48,895 --> 01:00:50,897
I almost fell for him.

869
01:01:18,216 --> 01:01:21,969
I wonder if she got home safely.

870
01:02:47,889 --> 01:02:50,516
My life's been like cotton candy,
unlike how it usually is.

871
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:52,185
I can't believe you admitted that.

872
01:02:53,102 --> 01:02:55,062
It's all over now.

873
01:02:55,146 --> 01:02:57,231
I'm just not that good of a person.

874
01:02:57,315 --> 01:03:00,026
I promise that nothing will happen.
You don't need to worry.

875
01:03:00,234 --> 01:03:02,236
-Dongbaek.
-Don't come here again.

876
01:03:03,821 --> 01:03:05,448
Gyu-tae!

877
01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:08,910
If you want to take me somewhere,
how about a motel?

878
01:03:09,577 --> 01:03:11,245
Should I just kill them all?

879
01:03:12,121 --> 01:03:13,956
-I caught someone last night.
-Who?

880
01:03:14,040 --> 01:03:16,125
-Why aren't you finishing your sentence?
-Let me go.

881
01:03:16,209 --> 01:03:17,877
-I told you not to hold her hand.
-Yong-sik.

